600000 people failed to exchange their driving license
600000 drivers missed the deadline to exchange their old driver’s license, whose validity expires at the end of the year.
Today is the last day on which you can apply for the exchange so that the authorities can issue a new driver’s license by the end of the year.
However, the ministry does not fear that after New Year, hundreds of thousands of drivers will go on the roads without a valid driving licence.
According to the authorities, mainly those who do not want to drive anymore did not exchange their driving license.
While small towns report a sharp drop in interest in the firing bill exchange, the capital’s offices are flooded with applications, and interest in the exchange grew this week.
The city administration handles around 2,000 customers every day.
You have to wait about half an hour.
In Prague, about 140,000 drivers have not yet exchanged their driving licences.
The issue of a new driving licence lasts 20 days.
But it is possible to apply for the exhibition with a shortened period of five days.
In this case, the driver must pay 500 crowns.
Drivers who do not make the required exchange by the end of the year and leave without a valid driver’s license, are threatened with a fine from January.
The offender pays a maximum of 2000 crowns.
However, the police can also have it applied with a reminder in the event of the violation.
In the event of a violation, the penalty may increase to 2,500 crowns.
According to previous information, even those who do not drive can be punished by the municipality.
He could, it was said, threaten a punishment of even 30,000 crowns.
The ministry has already called on the offices to exercise mildness and to impose at most a penalty of 1,000 crowns.
According to the spokesperson of the Ministry of Transport, Karel Hanzelka, but nobody threatens a thousand-crown penalty.
The driver's license is a document where everyone can decide whether they want to own it or not.
It is not an identity card that everyone, including a valid one, must have.
People who don’t want to drive should give up their driver’s license.
It suffices to take him to the competent municipal office or to send him there by registered letter.
At the end of the year, driving licences issued between 1964 and 1993 become invalid.
However, drivers must gradually also exchange other types of driving licenses.
People with driving licences from 1994 to 2000 have three more years to exchange.
The validity of licences issued from 2001 to 2004 will end in December 2013.
