The inmate lists of the concentration camps or the arrest warrants issued by the Gestapo had been assembled after the war for a practical reason: to find civilians who had been deported or subjected to forced labour, and possibly to provide them with evidence of their arrest, in order to pave the way for their compensation.
More than 300 permanent employees still process tens of thousands of personal requests in Bad Arolsen today.
