Congress agrees with the MIFID directive, which came into force on November 1.
In parallel with the parliamentary drafting, which today ended its meeting with the congressional decision in the Senate on the supplementary/amending amendments to the project, the government published the provisions resulting from the new law, with the intention of allowing the entry into force of both regulations by the end of the year.
The representatives of the various companies unanimously praised the efforts of Congress and Senate MPs, who had in their negotiations and voting the goal of establishing the best possible regulation that ensures the safety of investors and regulates the individual entrepreneurial activities in order to ensure a generally efficient market.
In addition to the modernisation of the financial markets, MIFID, which re-establishes the Securities Services Regulation, is pursuing an improvement in investor protection, an increase in the control entitlement of the Spanish Securities Commission (CNMV) and the promotion of cooperation between the various control authorities of the European Union.
The new Directive enables financial advisory services to be provided to both specialised companies and to natural or legal persons, and also contributes to the establishment of new financial services companies (ESIS), the advisory companies that are affiliated with the investment and brokerage companies of securities.
In addition, it extends the number of financial transaction execution systems, adding to regulated markets the multilateral securities trading systems and the internationalization of trade contracts, which would eventually compete with current economic operators.
The law obliges investment companies to disclose the focal points of their company profile, confrontation and forms of dealing with risks on the market, and to register all projects carried out in order to facilitate the CNMV’s control task.
The Economic Commission of Congress provided for further changes in retrospect, with the decision that the titled bond now has to be considered complex financial means for the investor due to its high degree of risk, confirmed by the US mortgage and banking crisis.
In addition, the entry into force of the directive was used to legally limit the areas of work of graduate economists; 30 years after 1977, the regulation restricting the areas of work reserved for economists was adopted.
The Senate, for its part, established new positions in the financial sector, such as that of the economic mediator, who works on a third-party account, does not require authorization from the CNMV and can simultaneously offer its services for commercialization of products and customer acquisition to several investment companies.
