Which insurance is best for me?
The car insurance, which covers a possible damage caused by the driver, involves a high cost, the amount of which again depends on various factors, e.g., age, gender, time of the creation of the driver's license, marital status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even harder to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, it must be clear what we are dealing with here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurance policyholder.
This agreement shall be recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract which stipulates that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and is obliged in return to present the corresponding compensation amount in the event of damages.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance that is composed of several factors, including age, gender, time of creation of the driver's license, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that higher contributions are also due in the event of a higher risk of accident.
For this reason, both over 25-year-olds and women have to make fewer contributions, because statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate due to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, since according to the statistical values and therefore also according to the conviction of the companies, they tend to have fewer accidents than single persons.
The benefit that is given to the vehicle affects the frequency of driving and thus the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
When setting up the premium, insurance companies must take into account a number of points.
For this reason, the driver must also study the situation thoroughly in order to select exactly the car insurance that best meets his personal needs.
At this point, we now list the most important points to consider when choosing an insurance policy in order to be able to make not only a performance-oriented, but also a price-oriented choice.
The under 25-year-olds encounter numerous obstacles when choosing an inexpensive insurance, such as the low driving practice and the young driver's license.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance cover to take out a full insurance, there are still cheaper alternatives.
The cautious drivers can choose a full insurance with deductible, so that the benefits of a full insurance are covered, but offered at a low price.
This type of contract implies that the customer has to pay part of the amount caused by the damage himself.
The amount is determined before the conclusion of the contract and on the basis of the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher the lower the amount to be paid, explains Luis Noguera, principal representative of Spain at First Europa, an online insurance brokerage company.
Another option is the extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accident damage, but not against the damage caused to the own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you’re under 25, it’s up to you to lower your insurance costs; this will increase your credit by trying to drive cautiously and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate at the relevant insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment involves an increase in said tariffs.
The amount of credits and penalty payments depends on the company and its earnings.
If the company has a profitable year behind it, it may allow itself to increase bonus payments, Noguera explains.
As soon as the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to sign a contract, due to the fact that with increasing driving practice, the accident rate decreases.
Thus, it is most sensible to opt for a full insurance with a deductible.
Normally, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, explains the Spanish head of the European company, adding that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice after the fear of the beginner has been dropped.
Nevertheless, it is more advisable for a married customer who does not have children to take out a full insurance policy; of course, only if the financial situation of the person in question permits.
On the part of the insurers, married couples with children are considered to be the customers with the lowest accident rate, and accordingly their contributions are also low.
In this case, a full insurance with a deductible (at an amount of around 300 euros) would be the best option. In the event that you have received a high credit, an extended insurance policy is recommended, which only starts for the third year of the vehicle.
They drive more relaxed overall and have a greater purchasing power, which allows them to make a higher contribution payment, notes Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, it is advisable to take out a full insurance with a deductible (at an amount of around 150 euros), or an extended insurance that only starts with a sufficiently high credit.
Ultimately, it must be noted that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver from possible accident damage, but also because it carries high costs that require that a thorough selection be made that corresponds to our personal situation.
